This program trains individuals to work in Los Angeles’ dynamic film and television industry. Those interested in applying for admissions should first get a medical certificate from an FAA-certified doctor. Applicants must also be at least 17 years old. Description: Foam Applications, a spray polyurethane foam roof contractor.
Full Description: Foam Applications is a licensed and insured Spray Polyurethane Foam (SPF) roofing contractor. Foam Applications single focus is the installation and maintenance of SPF roofing systems for commercial and industrial applications. SPF Roofing Systems provide many benefits to building owners. The two primary benefits are waterproofing and insulation value. Many additional benefits exist such as durability, longevity, lightweight, self-flashing, and strength especially with pre-engineered metal buildings. SPF is applied as a liquid using two-component spray equipment as it is applied onto the roof surface filling cracks and crevices. It expands approximately 20 times its original liquid volume to form a hard, monolithic roof surface. The polyurethane foam dries within seconds after application and is fully adhered to the roof surface with a history of lasting more than 35 years as a maintainable roofing medium. Its expansion results in a weather-tight roofing that is not only light weight, adding little weight to the structure of the building, but increasing the insulation value of the roof a measureable amount which should be relected in the heating and cooling of the building.

Industries: Assisted Living, Computer Vision, Elder Care
Description: Heron Point Tech build tech-based amenities to enhance the assisted living experience
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Between 2015 and 2030, the number of people in the world aged 60 years or over is expected to grow by 56%, from just over 900 million to nearly 1.5 billion. This trend in turn leads to an increase in the number of people requiring long-term skilled care (LTSC), which includes home care, hospices, nursing homes, and assisted living centers. One of the most common issues in LTSC settings is falls. One in every 3 people older than 65 years is estimated to fall 1 or more times each year. Fall death rates among adults age 65 and older increased more than 30% from 2007 to 2016. Every 19 minutes, an older adult dies from a fall. Falls in older adults are not only risky, but also costly. In 2019, falls of US residents aged 65 or older led to $51B in medical costs, with $39B paid for by Medicare/Medicaid and $12B paid by private entities. Falls are also the 2nd largest reason for lawsuits against LTSCs. Heron Point Tech’s Fall Prevention System allows assisted living facilities to preemptively and continuously detect residents who are likely to fall. As opposed to most fall-related systems, our system doesn’t detect falls - it stops them from happening in the first place. By using our camera-based system to track resident walking patterns/gaits, residents are assigned weekly fall risk scores. No wearable devices required.
